<h4 class="western"><span style="color: #080809;"><span style="font-family: inherit;"><span style="font-size: medium;"><b>The False Narrative: $1 Billion Cut to Schools?</b></span></span></span></h4>
The media and news outlets are screaming about a supposed $1 billion cut to school food programs. But here’s what they won’t tell you: the cut was to the <strong>Commodity Credit Corporation (CCC)</strong>, not directly to school meals. According to the USDA itself, "CCC does not have any employees." So, are you seriously going to hand $1 billion to a corporation with no staff? Where the hell does that money go? Notice who’s complaining the loudest—mainly Democrats in politics. (Let’s be clear: this site and I are about <strong>truth</strong>, not political affiliation.) How many people are getting private kickbacks from this shadowy fund? That’s the real question.

